  "title" : "How does Spring uses ThreadLocal variables",
  "body" : "<p>I would like to know some details on how Spring uses <code>Thread local</code> variables in managing EntityManagers.</p>\n<p>My model is the following:</p>\n<pre><code>@Transactional\npublic class MyClass \n{\n  @PersistenceContext\n  private EntityManager entityManager;\n\n    public void toSomethingTx()  \n    {...}\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>Let's consider the class above, which is a class annotated with <code>@Transactional</code> and uses an entity manager, when the entity manager is injected what is injected is really a proxy class that looks for the actual entitymanager in the <strong>ThreadScope</strong> to propagate the calls.</p>\n<p>This way each thread managing a user request is bound to its own entity manager.</p>\n<p>It would be great if you could validate my model and/or add more information about this.<br />\nThanks</p>\n"
}